content:
The General Liability line of business gives you a fully functional example of the General Liability product models, rating procedures, and business processes for quoting.

You can use this application for reference or as a base to develop your own product models and business processes.

Product Models and Rating Procedures:

* Product Model: General Liability
* Rating Procedure: Rating_GeneralLiability

The product model provides the structure for data that moves through business processes. The rating procedures take information from the prospective customer and calculate prices for coverages, then the product model rating simulation rolls up those prices and calculates the total premium.

To learn more about these product models and rating procedures, see General Liability Product Model and General Liability Rating.

Business Processes:

* Commercial Quote Business Process

This process guides prospective customers to get a rated quote for a commercial product. The process uses the General Liability product model and rating procedure to calculate prices for coverages.

Now that you've got a high-level intro to the General Liability line of business, look at the General Liability Product Model.
title: General Liability Insurance Overview
